Bash: A shell and command language used for automating tasks in Unix-like operating systems. It is excellent for file manipulation, command execution, and chaining tools together.

Python: A high-level, general-purpose programming language known for its readability and extensive libraries. It is widely used in cybersecurity for scripting, tool development, and data analysis.

Ruby: A dynamic, object-oriented programming language with a focus on simplicity and productivity. It is the language behind the Metasploit Framework.

PowerShell: A task automation and configuration management framework from Microsoft, consisting of a command-line shell and an associated scripting language. It is tightly integrated with the Windows operating system.

